				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Unable to target horses in PoN from below now?<a name="38143"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 4 04 3:24 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In order to pull the plateau using Eye of Zomm, you have to summon the eye right up against the wall while facing it, then run the eye up the 'crease' in the wall. If you summon it on the ground, I have yet to find a way to get it to 'climb' to the plateau. A bonus to this method is that you can pull all 4 horsies (one at a time) if you like, I haven't tried getting the eye into the mephit cave yet. Pretty sure I wouldn't have sufficient range to do much, but you could probably have some interesting fun using the bind-sight song in conjunction with it.
<br />

<br />
Once you have a horsie targeted, you can use the 'last target' key after your charm-swarm pull to sick yer pet on it. 
<br />

<br />
I tried the 'float real high' method suggested above and have yet to be able to target anything through the invisowall.
<br />

<br />
Be careful. The latest PoN stealth revamp has really upped the stun factor for random hits. (At least) Two of the hobbies now wander up and down the wall, and the Scourge and Painwracked both have a snare spell and will buff any nearby hobbies given time. The aggro range and melee range is also significantly larger for both NettWraiths and Hobbies. It'll catch you by surprise the first time it happens, but once you adjust, it's business as usual. The good news is that the hobbies no longer warp after the last stealth revamp nor have i adhered to any tree trunks. The tree canopies will still lock you in autoduck mode, freezing you in place,  until something comes along to put you out of your misery. I would suggest staying well away from the trees with lev on.
<br />

<br />
Glad it's workin for ya! 
<br />

<br />
-Savidge
<br />
Quellious</span></td>
